name: testing-rules
description: Testing standards for Rails 8
glob: test/**/*.rb

---
When writing tests:

1. Test Organization
- Use appropriate test type (unit, integration, system)
- Follow Rails testing directory structure
- Keep tests focused and atomic
- Use descriptive test names

2. FactoryBot Usage
- Keep factories minimal
- Use traits for variations
- Use sequences for unique values
- Follow factory naming conventions
- Test factories themselves

3. System Tests
- Use Capybara best practices
- Test JavaScript interactions
- Test responsive behavior
- Test Turbo and Stimulus features
- Use proper screen sizes

4. Test Data
- Don't use fixtures
- Use FactoryBot
- Clean up test data
- Use transactional fixtures
- Avoid database-specific features

5. Performance
- Use parallel testing
- Keep tests fast
- Avoid unnecessary database queries
- Use proper setup and teardown

6. Coverage
- Test happy paths
- Test edge cases
- Test error conditions
- Test security concerns
- Test accessibility features 